125, \"to\": 2130}, {\"ngram\": \"his flotilla\", \"from\": 2135, \"to\": 2147}, {\"ngram\": \"an aesthetic one\", \"from\": 2152, \"to\": 2168}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The Seine is a beautiful river (if not quite as grand as the Thames, I demur, as a Londoner), and Paris a beautiful city.\", \"from\": 2170, \"to\": 2291, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2174, \"end\": 2179, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 9.266434410778868e-35, \"text\": \"Seine\", \"types\": [\"Q47521\", \"Q4022\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\"}, {\"begin\": 2268, \"end\": 2273, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 4.536253317922161e-39, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a beautiful river\", \"from\": 2183, \"to\": 2200}, {\"ngram\": \"the Thames\", \"from\": 2227, \"to\": 2237}, {\"ngram\": \"a Londoner\", \"from\": 2251, \"to\": 2261}, {\"ngram\": \"a beautiful city\", \"from\": 2274, \"to\": 2290}]}, {\"sentence\": \"But French weather is scarcely less fickle than the British climate, and as the torchbearers set off down the Travers\\u00e9e de Paris, the \\\"City of Light\\\", as Hazel Irvine introduced it, was bathed in cloud.\", \"from\": 2292, \"to\": 2494, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2296, \"end\": 2302, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"score\": 0.9999943858404802, \"rank\": 5.614170465950198e-06, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q315\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\"}, {\"begin\": 2344, \"end\": 2351, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\", \"score\": 0.9999999998135536, \"rank\": 1.3126107300031339e-10, \"text\": \"British\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": 